"v. 轻轻倒出 【英】 v. 将...自瓶中倒入另一 容器(pour off gently) v. 将(液体, 如: 酒)自瓶中轻轻倒入另一容器(而不搅动沉淀物) 【记】这么变态的单词也考? dec(12月的缩写), ant蚂蚁: 有爱好养蚂蚁的吗? 到了12月, 天气冷了, 要把蚂蚁从薄的瓶子里挪到厚的瓶子里, 别光顾着给自己加被子! De向下, can罐头, t: 罐头向下－轻到 【类】subterfuge: deceive = decant: pour 讬词是小欺骗 = 轻轻倒出是小倾泻 【记】de 去掉 + can罐 + 头，将罐头去掉就是翻转倒掉 decant (v.)  1630s, ""pour off the clear liquid from a solution by gently tipping the vessel,"" originally an alchemical term, from French décanter, perhaps from Medieval Latin decanthare ""to pour from the edge of a vessel,"" from de- + Medieval Latin canthus ""corner, lip of a jug,"" from Latin cantus, canthus ""iron rim around a carriage wheel."" Related: Decanted; decanting."
